# Development Workflow

This project follows an AI-assisted development workflow powered by [claude-workflow](https://github.com/{{WORKFLOW_REPO}}).

## Lifecycle Overview

```
IDEA → [/draft] → BACKLOG → [/refine] → READY → [/implement] → IN-PROGRESS → [/pr] → DONE
                                                                                        ↓
                                                                               [/release] → RELEASED
```

## Commands

| Command | Phase | What it does |
|---------|-------|-------------|
| `/brainstorm` | Planning | Analyze project + generate backlog ideas with you |
| `/prioritize` | Planning | Rank backlog against vision, pick next-version items |
| `/draft feature "title"` | Draft | Create raw backlog entry (no planning needed) |
| `/draft bug "title"` | Draft | Report a bug |
| `/refine FEAT-001` | Refinement | RE + Tech Planner iterate until spec is ready |
| `/implement FEAT-001` | Implementation | Tests first (isolated context), then code |
| `/commit` | Implementation | Quality-gated conventional commit |
| `/pr [base]` | Review | CI → code review → security review → auto-merge |
| `/release patch\|minor\|major` | Release | Version bump + changelog + tag + publish |
| `/resume` | Recovery | Continue interrupted in-progress work |
| `/unsupervised on\|off` | Autonomy | No questions, autonomous defaults, loop-safe |
| `/workflow-decisions [setting]` | Config | View/change a workflow setting; syncs the skill + `decisions.md` |
| `/workflow-update` | Maintenance | Update workflow plugin to latest version |

Questions about the process? Just ask — the `workflow-coach` agent answers from these docs without loading them into your session.

## Configuration

Every tunable setting (refine sizing defaults, testing scope, review tier, branching model, auto-merge, GitHub integration, …) is documented in [`decisions.md`](decisions.md). That file is the human-readable **record** — each setting's live value lives in the skill that uses it for speed. Change any setting with **`/workflow-decisions`**, which edits the live value and updates `decisions.md` together so they never drift.

## Specs

Specs live in `docs/specs/`:
- `backlog/` — raw drafts, not yet refined
- `ready/` — refined, DoR met, ready to implement
- `completed/` — implemented and merged

## Quality Gates

| Gate | When | Who |
|------|------|-----|
| Auto-format | Every file edit | Hook |
| Tests | Per subtask (during implement) | Claude locally |
| CI: lint + typecheck + tests + security + build | Every PR | GitHub Actions |
| Code review | After CI passes | `code-reviewer` agent |
| Security review | After CI passes | `security-reviewer` agent |
| Architect review | After CI passes (structural changes) | `architect-reviewer` agent |
| Documentation | After all tests green | `documentation-writer` agent |
